<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>embarrassed at something • embarrassed with something</xh5><p> <i>embarrassed at something—</i>feeling unease or mental discomfort about smth.: She’s embarrassed—<u>embarrassed at</u> being so successful in a profession where so many fail.</p><p> <i>embarrassed with something—</i>1. hindered in one’s movements or experiencing physical difficulties because of smth.: Seeing he was <u>embarrassed with</u> his luggage, I offered to help him. 2. <i>= embarrassed at something:</i> Many kids don’t want to be <u>embarrassed with</u> being escorted out, even if it’s a friendly escort.</p> </entry>
